Pick n Pay and Woolworths are asking consumers to return products suspected to be contaminated with listeria South African kitchens and stores across the country are all in a bit of a frenzy at the moment, following Health Minister Dr Aaron Motsoaledi announcing that his department had finally tracked the source of the listeriosis outbreak. While Enterprise may be the source of the problem, major retailers have announced other products that should also be returned immediately. Just because it isn’t an Enterprise product, doesn’t mean it’s safe to eat, folks. People are encouraged to put the products in a plastic bag and return it to the store to receive a full refund. READ MORE: Tiger Brands recalls Enterprise processed meats over listeriosis fears WAFERTHIN CHARGRILLED HAM 125G
